text: Bradford is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in Franklin County, Iowa, United States. Its population was 99 as of the 2010 census. Bradford was platted in 1906. ==Demographics== ==Notes== Category:Census-designated places in Iowa Category:Census-designated places in Franklin County, Iowa Category:1906 establishments in Iowa Category:Populated places established in 1906
